        "faq_section_main": {
          "type": "faq_section",
          "settings": {
            "q1": "How is this different from the Dyson Airwrap?",
            "a1": "<p>The Mammoth AirStyler uses the same Coanda airflow technology as the Dyson Airwrap. The difference? Price. You get salon-quality results for under $100 instead of $600. Same technology, smart pricing.</p>",
            "q2": "Will it damage my hair?",
            "a2": "<p>No. Unlike flat irons and curling irons that use extreme direct heat (up to 230°C), the AirStyler uses controlled airflow with a max temperature of 110°C. Your hair gets styled without getting fried.</p>",
            "q3": "How long does styling take?",
            "a3": "<p>Most styles take under 10 minutes. Dry, curl, or straighten — all with the same tool. No switching between dryer, brush, and iron.</p>",
            "q4": "Does it work on all hair types?",
            "a4": "<p>Yes. The 3 temperature settings (60°C, 85°C, 110°C) let you adjust for fine, medium, or thick hair. The ceramic coating ensures even heat distribution regardless of hair type.</p>",
            "q5": "What's included in the Complete Kit vs Base Unit?",
            "a5": "<p>The Complete Kit ($99.90) includes the base unit, all 5 attachments, travel pouch, heat protectant spray, silk scrunchie, and digital e-book. The Base Unit ($79.90) includes just the unit and attachments.</p>",
            "q6": "What if I don't like it?",
            "a6": "<p>We offer a 30-day return policy — no questions asked. Plus every AirStyler comes with a 1-year warranty. We stand behind our products.</p>",
            "q7": "Is it safe to use? Any certifications?",
            "a7": "<p>Yes. The Mammoth AirStyler is UL 1727 certified for electrical safety. The 360° swivel cord and ceramic coating are designed for safe daily use.</p>",
            "q8": "Can I travel with it?",
            "a8": "<p>The Complete Kit includes a travel pouch for easy packing. Note: the unit is rated for 110-120V / 60Hz (US standard). For international travel, you'll need a voltage converter.</p>"
